title: SAMURAIS
name: Isabel Dos Santos.
details: Our Senshi Samurais Team is for 3-4 year olds.This class is an introduction to physical movement, team work and a class environment . Students learn to roll, fall safely, work together, turn take and the basic skills of Judo.The program runs for 6 weeks in the middle of each school term. These classes are designed to help students learn about their bodies, begin to develop strength & coordination and prepare them to graduate in to our Ninjas class.Classes are taught by Ivo and Isabel Dos Santos.

title: TITANS
name: KIM CHALMERS
details: Our Titans Team is a class for 11-14 year olds.Students in this class learn the more advanced movements of Judo and develop their physicality in preparation for integration in to Adults Judo. The Titans train 3 times a week with the Saturday session being a joint session with the Fundamentals Adults Class.

title: ADVANCED JUDO
name: BAK SUKARI
details: Judo is a Japanese Martial Art & Olympic Sport focusing on using your opponent’s weight & strength against them.Judo training provides a unique physical and mental workout while developing & improving your balance, co-ordination & confidence.This training involves throwing techniques, pins, arm locks & choking techniques.Judo translated from Japanese simply means “The Gentle Way.”
